<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Va. Child Stabbed in Front of Home  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALEXANDRIA, Va. (AP) -- An 8-year-old boy was stabbed to death
Wednesday while playing with other children in front of his
great-grandmother's home in what police described as a random
attack.
</P>
<P>
   The great-grandmother and another woman also were stabbed while
trying to help the boy before the suspect, a man in his 20s, fled.
He remained at large Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Shifflett was killed in an ''apparently random attack,''
police Lt. John Crawford said.
</P>
<P>
   Police did not know the suspect's identity, the motive or if the
child and his assailant knew each other.
</P>
<P>
   The 51-year-old woman who tried to help was hospitalized in
guarded but stable condition at Washington Hospital Center. The
great-grandmother, 80, suffered cuts to her hand and was at
Alexandria Hospital with injuries not considered life-threatening.
The identities of both were withheld.
</P>
</TEXT>
