<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hershiser Ties NL Record  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Orel Hershiser tied a modern-day National
League record Wednesday by hitting four batters -- in just 1 1-3
innings -- in Los Angeles' game against Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Hershiser, pitching despite a slight groin muscle pull, matched
the record of four hit batters in one game shared by seven others,
the last the Dodgers' Tom Candiotti in 1997, also against Houston.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers pitcher hit Richard Hidalgo and pitcher Shane
Reynolds in the first inning, then hit Jeff Bagwell and Hidalgo
again in the second.
</P>
<P>
   Hershiser gave up seven runs on four hits and two walks, and he
also threw several pitches into the dirt and several others to the
backstop during his brief stint.
</P>
<P>
   All three of the Astros he hit remained in the game, and none
made threatening gestures toward the pitcher.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
