this year because the rate has declined each decade since 1970 --
from 78 percent to 75 percent in 1980 and 65 percent in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   In New Jersey, the overall census response rate in 1990 was 65
percent. The latest figures put this year's response rate at 66
percent.
