<HEADLINE> Bomb Explodes in Pakistan  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAHORE, Pakistan (AP) -- A bomb exploded Thursday outside the
headquarters of Pakistan's right-wing religious party, police said.
</P>
<P>
   There were no reports of injuries or damage in the explosion in
Mansura, 10 miles south of Lahore, officials said. No one took
responsibility for the bombing, and police refused to speculate.
</P>
<P>
   Jamaat-e-Islami is a small, but powerful religious party that is
considered the best organized of the religious parties in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
   In recent weeks, Pakistan has been wracked by religiously
motivated violence involving attacks on the country's minority
Shiite Muslims, who have blamed militant Sunni Muslims, the
majority Islamic sect here.
</P>
<P>
   There was no evidence, however, to link the bombing to these
attacks.
</P>
</TEXT>
