Gunman Kills Two in Arizona
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
	   PEORIA, Ariz. (AP) -- A man who feuded with a retirement community
association barged into the group's meeting armed with a rifle and handguns and
opened fire Wednesday, police said. Two women were killed and four others
injured. Police arrested Richard Glassel, 61, a former resident at Ventana Lakes
community in suburban Phoenix. Neighbors and witnesses said Glassel had past
run-ins with the community association, which was meeting Wednesday afternoon at
the community recreation center. Glassel was tackled and subdued by people in
the center when his gun jammed.
