<HEADLINE> Prison doctor accused of having sex with an inmate  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   MALONE, N.Y. (AP) -- An upstate prison doctor is charged with
third-degree sodomy and has been suspended without pay after
allegedly having sexual relations with an inmate.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Waqar A. Farooqi, 35, of Malone, worked at Bare Hill
Correctional Facility, a medium-security state prison about 40
miles west of Plattsburgh. He was freed on $10,000 bail following
an arraignment at Malone village court.
</P>
<P>
   ''This was a result of an on-going investigation by our
Inspector General's Office, specifically the Sex Crimes Division,''
said Department of Corrections spokesman Michael Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Farooqi, who is Pakistani, holds a limited license to practice
medicine in New York state and has been a member in good standing
with no disciplinary charges against him, according to a
spokeswoman at the State Professional Licensing Bureau. He had been
a clinical physician at the facility since February 1997 and was
earning $98,625 a year.
</P>
