<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 10:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nissan Recalls '95, '96 Sentras  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GARDENA, Calif. (AP) -- Nissan Motor Co. has announced a safety
recall on about 14,500 Nissan Sentra vehicles because a front coil
spring is susceptible to corrosion.
</P>
<P>
   The spring could deteriorate on some of these vehicles if they
are operated in areas where a significant amount of salt is used to
rid streets of snow, the company said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Corrosion of the spring causes it to break and possibly puncture
a tire, which could cause the driver to lose control of the
vehicle.
</P>
<P>
   The recall affects only 1995 and 1996 model year Nissan Sentras
built in 1995 between May and November. The repair is free and
takes about two hours to perform.
</P>
<P>
   The springs do not need to be replaced unless the car has been
used on salty roads, Nissan officials said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
