<HEADLINE> Tornados Destroy Kansas Homes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PARSONS, Kan. (AP) -- A line of severe storms stretching from
Kansas to Missouri unleashed at least four tornados that destroyed
homes, flattened a carnival and caused several minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
   ''We were able to get the sirens off in time and that made a big
difference,'' said Keith Stammer, public information officer in
Labette County.
</P>
<P>
   About 10 homes were demolished when a tornado hit Parsons on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is nothing like we've ever seen in Parsons,'' said Martha
Walters, an administrative assistant. ''We've never had damage like
this.''
</P>
<P>
   Power was restored Thursday morning in the town of 13,000 about
150 miles south of Kansas City. The storm also destroyed a
carnival, scattering Ferris wheel parts. No serious injuries were
reported.
</P>
<P>
   Other tornados touched down in Walnut, Cherryvale and Eire in
southeastern Kansas.
</P>
<P>
   The severe weather included heavy rain, large hail and
straight-line winds, according to the National Weather Service.
</P>
</TEXT>
