<HEADLINE> Bank One's CFO To Resign  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Bank One Corp.'s chief financial officer Robert
Rosholt has become the latest executive to leave the company, which
is completing a turnover of top managers after months of turmoil.
</P>
<P>
   The nation's fourth-biggest bank holding company said a search
is under way to replace Rosholt, who it said has decided to resign
May 1.
</P>
<P>
   Rosholt, 50, has served as chief financial officer of Bank One
since the 1998 merger of Columbus, Ohio-based Banc One Corp. and
First Chicago NBD Corp.
</P>
<P>
   His departure follows by four months the resignation of chairman
and chief executive officer John McCoy, who was succeeded in the
post last month by James Dimon.
</P>
<P>
   McCoy was under fire for problems that caused Bank One's stock
to start plummeting last August when it acknowledged it was losing
credit-card customers due to flawed strategies.
</P>
</TEXT>
