<P>
   Dow Ends Up 169; Nasdaq Falls 62
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks rose sharply today on the
latest round of strong corporate profit reports. Technology stocks
ended modestly lower as investors took some profits from big gains
of Monday and Tuesday and struggled to chart a course in the
volatile sector. The Dow Jones industrial average rose 169.09 to
close at 10,844.05. The Dow ended the four-day week with a gain of
538.28 points, or 5.2 percent. The Nasdaq composite index fell
62.61 to close at 3,643.80. Even with losses Wednesday and today,
the Nasdaq rose 322.51 points, or 9.7 percent, for the week after
plummeting a record 25.3 percent the previous week. Broader
indicators were mostly higher. Financial markets will be closed
Friday for the observance of Good Friday. Bond markets closed at 2
