jobs to streamline operations following its acquisition of
Consolidated Natural Gas Co. of Pittsburgh, the company said today.
The parent company of Virginia Power expects to save $75 million
this year as a result of the job cuts, which will include early
retirements and layoffs.Bill Mistr, a Dominion vice president, said
the vast majority of the positions are in corporate support
services in Richmond and Pittsburgh.
</P>
