</P>
<P>
   NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Yale University is being dropped as a
defendant in a lawsuit filed by the heavy metal rock band
Metallica. The move comes after Yale agreed to block access from
its computer network to a Web site that allows people to trade
copyrighted music. Yale blocked access to the site last week after
Metallica filed a lawsuit against the school, two other
universities and California-based Napster, which makes the popular
Internet music sharing software.
