<HEADLINE> Two upstate New York banks merge  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NORWICH, N.Y. (AP) -- NBT Bancorp Inc. said Thursday it is
acquiring a rival upstate New York bank holding company, BSB
Bancorp Inc., for $251 million in stock.
</P>
<P>
   Norwich-based NBT Bancorp operates NBT Bank, which has 36
offices in nine counties in central and northern New York.
Binghamton-based BSB Bancorp's banking subsidiary, BSB Bank &AMP;
Trust, operates 22 offices in six counties in central and western
New York.
</P>
<P>
   The companies said they have signed a definitive agreement to
join forces late this year, creating one of upstate New York's
largest independent community banks with more than 55 offices in 12
counties and $4.7 billion in assets.
</P>
<P>
   Under the deal, which is subject to regulatory approval, BSB
shareholders would get two shares of NBT common stock for each BSB
share. That amounts to a premium of 34 percent over BSB's price of
$17.87 1/2 on the Nasdaq Stock Market on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   BSB Bancorp employs about 600 people and NBT Bancorp has 900
employees. Fewer than 100 jobs will be eliminated by the merger,
said Thomas Thorn, BSB Bancorp's acting president.
</P>
</TEXT>
