<HEADLINE> Food Makers Warn of Ingredients  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Two food manufacturers issued warnings
Thursday that their products contain items not listed on the labels
but could cause allergies.
</P>
<P>
   Snyder of Berlin, Pa., said it voluntarily recalled 202 cases of
Naturally Low Fat Carmel Corn because they may contain peanuts that
are not listed on the label.
</P>
<P>
   And Gourmet Mixes, Inc., of Seattle, Wash., said it recalled all
bottle sizes and production codes of Demitri's Bloody Mary
Seasoning because they may contain egg yolk not listed on the
label.
</P>
<P>
   People with allergies to these foods could run the risk of
life-threatening reactions if they eat them.
</P>
<P>
   The 10-ounce packages of Snyder's Naturally Low Fat Carmel Corn
were distributed in Kentucky, Maryland, Ohio, Pennsylvania,
Tennessee, Virginia and West Virginia. They have the code 42May22
directly below the preprinted price of $1.75 on the front.
Consumers can return the item to the place of purchase for a
refund. Persons with questions can call 1-800-270-2743.
</P>
<P>
   The recalled Demitri's Bloody Mary Seasoning was distributed
nationally in retail stores and through catalogs in 5-ounce glass
bottles and 16-ounce and 64-ounce plastic bottles. Customers can
return the mix to the place of purchase for a refund. Those with
questions can call the manufacturer at 206-764-6006.
</P>
</TEXT>
