<HEADLINE> Seven Die in Brazil Bus Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAO PAULO, Brazil ---- A bus careened off a bridge early Thursday,
killing seven people and injuring 19, according to news reports.
</P>
<P>
   A blown tire may have caused the driver to lose control of the
bus, which fell nearly 20 feet from a bridge, CBN radio reported.
</P>
<P>
   The accident happened near Ribeirao Preto, some 200 miles
northwest of Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
   Many of the victims were in serious condition at nearby
hospitals, CBN said.
</P>
<P>
   A policeman in Ribeirao Preto said he could not provide any
information on the accident.
</P>
