<HEADLINE> Arizona To Activate Closer Mantei  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- Closer Matt Mantei has completed his last
rehabilitation appearance without any ill effects and will be
activated by the Arizona Diamondbacks on Friday, manager Buck
Showalter said.
</P>
<P>
   Mantei has been on the disabled list since April 2 with biceps
tendinitis. He made consecutive appearances for Triple-A Tucson on
Tuesday and Wednesday and experienced no pain in his arm.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday night, he threw 24 pitches while getting two outs.
Mantei walked two, gave up one hit and a run.
</P>
<P>
   The Diamondbacks will have to make a roster move to make room
for Mantei, but Showalter said an announcement would not be made
until Friday.
</P>
