<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stocks rose early Friday following a jump in
the Dow Jones industrial average on Wall Street. The dollar was
higher against the yen.
</P>
<P>
   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average gained 308.93
points, or 1.63 percent, to 19,268.25 points in the first 30
minutes of trading. On Thursday, the average closed down 127.30
points, or 0.67 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The dollar bought 105.80 yen, up 1.02 yen from late Thursday and
also above its late New York level of 105.73 yen.
</P>
<P>
   On the Tokyo stock market, prices moved broadly higher as
investors were cheered by the Dow's 169.09-point rise Thursday,
leaving the New York index at 10,844.05 at the market's close.
</P>
<P>
   Traders said, however, that some investors were cautious ahead
of a three-day Easter holiday weekend in the United States starting
Friday. New York markets will be closed April 21 in observance of
Good Friday, a national holiday.
</P>
<P>
   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the
first section was up 30.05 points, or 1.84 percent, to 1,659.05
points. The TOPIX closed up 9.18 points, or 0.56 percent, the day
before.
</P>
<P>
   In currency dealings, the dollar was lifted by remarks by
Japan's top central bank official reaffirming that the bank's
current credit policy will remain unchanged.
</P>
<P>
   In testimony before Japan's Parliament, Bank of Japan Governor
Masaru Hayami said Thursday the central bank will keep its current
zero-rate policy until deflation fears are gone.
</P>
<P>
   Lower interest rates tend to make a nation's currency less
attractive to investors.
</P>
<P>
   In other currencies, the euro was traded at 99.22 yen, up from
98.30 yen late Thursday in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   The yield on the benchmark 10-year Japanese government bond
stood at 1.7350 percent, unchanged from Thursday's finish. Its
price remained 101.42.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: Japan's Tokyo Stock Exchange: http://www.tse.or.jp./
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
