<HEADLINE> Nevin, Padres Manager Bochy Ejected  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. LOUIS (AP) -- San Diego Padres cleanup hitter Phil Nevin and
manager Bruce Bochy were ejected Thursday night in a dispute over a
called third strike.
</P>
<P>
   Nevin struck out to end the top of the third, and after going to
third base he badgered plate umpire Larry Young about the call.
Bochy also was ejected when he joined the argument.
</P>
<P>
   On his way off the field, Nevin threw his glove and hat in the
air and made a gesture in Young's direction with his arm. He then
took off his jersey and dropped it in foul territory.
</P>
<P>
   Young was the first base umpire on Eric Davis' controversial
two-run bases-loaded infield hit on Wednesday night, ruling him
safe when replays indicated Davis was out by a half-step.
</P>
<P>
   The Padres were trailing the St. Louis Cardinals 6-0.
</P>
